## LLM Data — Calling Edge Functions for Interpretation/Reasoning

Every RAD app uses LLM to interpret backend data or reason from user inputs. LLM calls go through Supabase Edge Functions (API keys are server-only). The frontend treats LLM responses as regular data — fetched via React Query, cached aggressively.

**Hook pattern for LLM interpretation:**

```typescript
// src/hooks/useInterpretation.ts
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { supabase } from "@/lib/supabase";

export function useInterpretation(resultData: unknown, enabled = true) {
  const inputHash = JSON.stringify(resultData);
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["interpretation", inputHash],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.functions.invoke("interpret-result", {
        body: { resultData },
      });
      if (error) throw error;
      return data as { interpretation: string };
    },
    enabled: enabled && !!resultData,
    staleTime: Infinity,  // Same input = same interpretation. Never re-fetch.
    retry: 1,
  });
}
```

**In the screen component** (after copying from Make):

```typescript
// Make's mock: hardcoded interpretation string
//   const interpretation = "Ngày Hoàng Đạo, Trực Thành — rất thuận lợi cho ký kết.";

// Replace with:
const { data: llm, isPending: llmLoading } = useInterpretation(resultData);
const interpretation = llm?.interpretation;

// Render: show result data immediately (from Supabase query)
// Show interpretation when ready, or skeleton while loading
// If LLM fails, screen still works — just without the interpretation text
```

**Key rules:**
- **staleTime: Infinity** for all LLM results — same input never re-calls LLM
- **Screen must work without LLM** — show raw data immediately, add interpretation as enhancement. Never block the screen on LLM loading.
- **`supabase.functions.invoke()`** — the correct way to call Edge Functions from the Supabase client. Automatically includes the user's JWT.
- **Never call LLM APIs directly from frontend** — no `fetch("https://openrouter.ai/...")` or any LLM API in components.
